{"questionId":"9741","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A particle, A, moves so that its velocity (<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\nu \">\n  <mi>ν</mi>\n</math></span> ms<sup>−1</sup>) at time <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> is given by <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\nu \">\n  <mi>ν</mi>\n</math></span> = 2 sin <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> ≥ 0.</p>\n<p>The kinetic energy (<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"E\">\n  <mi>E</mi>\n</math></span>) of the particle A is measured in joules (J) and is given by <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"E\">\n  <mi>E</mi>\n</math></span> = 5<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\nu \">\n  <mi>ν</mi>\n</math></span><sup>2</sup>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence or otherwise find the first time at which the kinetic energy is changing at&nbsp;a rate of 5 J s<sup>−1</sup>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> = 0.126 &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9741","referenceCode":"SPM.1.AHL.TZ0.7c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence or otherwise find the first time at which the kinetic energy is changing at a rate of 5 J s−1.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.9—Differentiating standard functions and derivative rules"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}